perniciem] Too strong a term to refer to any disgrace he may have sustained under Galba, or to his supersession (iv. 68. 2) in the command of the Praetorians. &Vc have no notice of his final fate.

3 defectione] Described at the end of Book ii.

4 Forum Alieni] Was it, like Vicetia (8. 2), connected with Caecina’s family? If so, his father or grandfather probably came to Cisalpine Gaul as an official, or he could scarcely have founded or given name to a Forum. Although the country was originally Tuscan, and in some districts remained so, the Caecinae seem to have belonged to the better known Tuscany, where there is a river of the same name.
